text: Randolph County is a county on the central eastern border of the U.S. state of Alabama. "ACES Randolph County Office" (links/history), Alabama Cooperative Extension System (ACES), 2007, webpage: ACES-Randolph. As of the 2020 census, the population was 21,967. The county seat is Wedowee. The name is in honor of John Randolph, a member of the United States Senate from Virginia. Randolph County was founded on December 18, 1832. == References == Category:1832 establishments in Alabama Category:Alabama counties
title: Randolph County, Alabama
